## Hints for Future Agents
- The commit-notes rule is in rules/commit-notes.md and applies globally.
- It complements the Chesterton's Fence rule in rules/simple.md — when
  doing fence checks, read git notes for agent context.
- Notes use a specific section format (Conversation, Actions, Errors &
  Mistakes, Dead Ends, Hints for Future Agents, Codebase Discoveries,
  Open Questions). Follow it.
- The "Reading Notes" section at the top is important — agents should
  check notes BEFORE modifying code with recent notes attached.

## Codebase Discoveries
- Rules files use a consistent style: markdown with headers, imperative
  tone, ALWAYS/NEVER/DO/PREFER keywords for directives.
- The abatilo-core plugin has a git-commit skill that handles the commit
  creation process. The commit-notes rule is separate and additive.

